---
import '../styles/global.css';
import SmallMultiples from '../components/SmallMultiples.astro';
import Dumbbell from '../components/Dumbbell.astro';
import BumpChart from '../components/BumpChart.astro';
---

<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <meta charset="utf-8" />
    <link rel="icon" type="image/svg+xml" href="/favicon.svg" />
    <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.googleapis.com" />
    <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.gstatic.com" crossorigin />
    <link
      href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Fraunces:ital,opsz,wght@0,9..144,400;0,9..144,500;0,9..144,600;0,9..144,700;0,9..144,800;0,9..144,900;1,9..144,400;1,9..144,600&family=Jost:wght@300;400;500;600&family=Tiro+Devanagari+Hindi:ital@0;1&display=swap"
      rel="stylesheet"
    />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width" />
    <meta name="generator" content={Astro.generator} />
    <title>Part II · The Big Eighteen · अठारह बड़े राज्य · India Census Explorer</title>
  </head>
  <body>
    <div class="grain" aria-hidden="true"></div>
    <div class="page">

      <div class="running-head">
        <a href="/" class="eyebrow back-link">← Part I</a>
        <span class="eyebrow dot">◇</span>
        <span class="eyebrow">Vol. II · Figs. 7–9</span>
        <span class="eyebrow dot">◇</span>
        <span class="eyebrow">State trajectories</span>
      </div>

      <hr class="rule double" />

      <header class="masthead">
        <div class="masthead-copy">
          <p class="kicker">Part the Second</p>
          <h1 class="title">
            <span class="title-en">The Big</span>
            <span class="title-en-b">Eighteen</span>
            <span class="title-hi">अठारह&nbsp;बड़े&nbsp;राज्य</span>
          </h1>
          <p class="lede">
            India has <b>28 states and 8 union territories</b>. This page
            follows the <em>eighteen largest</em> — the two of the East, two of
            the West, ten of the North (the Hindi belt, with Delhi) and four
            of the South. Together they contain roughly <b>93%</b> of the
            country's population. The remainder — the North-East, J&amp;K,
            Ladakh, Punjab, Goa and the smaller UTs — sits in the <em>Other</em>
            bucket of Part I and is not plotted here individually.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="masthead-figure" aria-hidden="true">
          <div class="glyph">¶</div>
          <div class="figure-no">No.<br /><b>2</b></div>
        </div>
      </header>

      <hr class="rule" />

      <SmallMultiples />

      <hr class="rule" />

      <Dumbbell />

      <hr class="rule" />

      <BumpChart />

      <hr class="rule double" />

      <aside class="next-step">
        <span class="smallcaps">close the volume</span>
        <a href="/" class="next-link">
          <span class="next-arrow">←</span>
          <span class="next-title">Return to Part I</span>
          <span class="next-subtitle hi">भाग एक पर लौटें</span>
        </a>
        <p class="next-blurb">
          Or begin again — the regional view is in Part I, with the representation
          argument that follows from it.
        </p>
      </aside>

      <footer class="colophon">
        <div class="colophon-col">
          <span class="smallcaps">§ source</span>
          <p>
            All state-level figures are taken directly from the Census of
            India, Table A-02 — same file as Part I. Values already backfilled
            to post-2000 state boundaries; Telangana merged with Andhra Pradesh.
            <a
              href="https://censusindia.gov.in/nada/index.php/catalog/43333"
              target="_blank"
              rel="noopener noreferrer"
            >— NADA 43333 →</a>
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="colophon-col">
          <span class="smallcaps">† on the cartographic absence</span>
          <p>
            This page tracks <b>eighteen</b> modern states: the two of the
            East, two of the West, ten of the North (Hindi belt) and four of
            the South. The North-East, Jammu &amp; Kashmir, Ladakh, Punjab,
            Goa, and the smaller Union Territories account for the residual
            and are not plotted individually here.
          </p>
        </div>
      </footer>

      <div class="running-foot">
        <span class="eyebrow">Set in Fraunces &amp; Tiro Devanagari Hindi</span>
        <span class="eyebrow dot">◇</span>
        <span class="eyebrow">Composed on cream</span>
      </div>
    </div>

    <script>
      requestAnimationFrame(() => {
        document.body.classList.add('ready');
      });
    </script>
  </body>
</html>
